title Physical Data Model: Hybrid Firebase Architecture (Next.js)

' --- CLOUD FIRESTORE (STATIC DATA) ---
package \"Cloud Firestore (Static Data)\" {
 
 object \"Collection: /users\" as Users
 object \"Doc: uid_123\" as UserDoc {
 role: \"DRIVER\"
 name: \"Ali Khan\"
 email: \"ali@uos.edu\"
 fcm_token: \"xyz...\"
 }

 object \"Collection: /buses\" as Buses
 object \"Doc: bus_01\" as BusDoc {
 plate: \"SGA-2025\"
 capacity: 45
 status: \"ACTIVE\"
 current_route: \"route_A\"
 }

 object \"Collection: /routes\" as Routes
 object \"Doc: route_A\" as RouteDoc {
 name: \"Campus Loop\"
 polyline: \"u{~vF_b}@\"
 stops: [StopObj, StopObj]
 }
}

' --- REALTIME DATABASE (LIVE DATA) ---
package \"Realtime Database (High Frequency)\" {
 
 object \"Node: /live_locations\" as Live
 object \"Key: bus_01\" as LocLog {
 lat: 32.0740
 lng: 72.6861
 speed: 40.5
 heading: 90
 timestamp: 172930400
 }
 
 object \"Node: /driver_sessions\" as Sess
 object \"Key: uid_123\" as SessLog {
 is_online: true
 last_ping: 172930405
 }
}

' --- ALIGNMENT & RELATIONSHIPS ---

' Force separation between Left and Right packages
Users -[hidden]right- Live

' Hierarchy Links
Users ||--o{ UserDoc : contains
Buses ||--o{ BusDoc : contains
Routes ||--o{ RouteDoc : contains

Live ||--o{ LocLog : streams
Sess ||--o{ SessLog : tracks

' Logical Connections (How they relate in code)
BusDoc ..> LocLog : \"ID Match (bus_01)\"
UserDoc ..> SessLog : \"ID Match (uid_123)\"
